notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
Rocky Enterprise Software Foundation Identity Management (IdM) is a centralized authentication, identity management, and authorization solution for both traditional and cloud-based enterprise environments. 

Bug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):

* IPA sidgen fails to create SID for manually set ID for a new range (JIRA:Rocky Linux-28996)

* The change for preventing deletion of the admin user caused a regression in disable (JIRA:Rocky Linux-34756)

* Need to change log file permissions of IPA as per CIS benchmark [rhel-8.10.z] (JIRA:Rocky Linux-38929)

* PSKC.xml issues with ipa_otptoken_import.py (JIRA:Rocky Linux-39616)

* kdc.crt certificate not getting automatically renewed by certmonger in IPA Hidden replica. [rhel-8.10.z] (JIRA:Rocky Linux-45908)

* Check hidden status for PKINIT certificate creation (JIRA:Rocky Linux-4913)

* ipa-crlgen-manage should unset ca.certStatusUpdateInterval on enable (JIRA:Rocky Linux-30280)

This advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.
